cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.CC

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper discusses a logical theory, Ludics, and its interpretation of Logic. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper deals with the structure of formulas or types, which are relevant to programming languages. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as Ludics can be used to model interaction and communication in multi-agent systems, which is a topic of interest in AI. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper discusses the decomposability of behaviours, which is related to the structure of data. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a possible category as Ludics can be used to study the complexity of proofs and computations.
